{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, there is no systematic approach for mapping technology tools into concrete requirements for the AI Act.",
    "Despite increased interest in the use of AI for data-driven, evidence-based policymaking (Gesk and Leyer, 2022), the development of practical systems that can be operationalized is in early stages.",
    "Some research works can be found in the broader context of data-driven policymaking that leverages Big Data (Hochtl et al., 2016).",
    "Some systems for data-driven policies take advantage of social media information (Bertot et al., 2011) based on different techniques, including data mining and ML algorithms (Charalabidis et al., 2015).",
    "There are also works on political analysis using statistical techniques, which is a foundation for ML (Monogan III, 2015)."
  ]
}